ew?) |work=canceled TV shows - TV Series Finale}}</ref>\n\n| link6     = Teen Wolf (season 6)\n| timeslot6 = Tuesday 9:00{{nbsp}}pm {{small|(Part 1)}}<br />Sunday 8:00{{nbsp}}pm {{small|(Part 2)}}\n| episodes6 = 20\n| start6    = {{Start date|2016|11|15}}\n| startrating6 = 0.57<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-tuesday-cable-originals-network-finals-11-15-2016.html |title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Tuesday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 11.15.2016 |last=Metcalf |first=Mitch |accessdate=November 23, 2016 |work=ShowBuzzDaily |date=November 16, 2016}}</ref>\n| end6      = {{End date|2017|9|24}}\n| endrating6   = 0.68<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-sunday-cable-originals-network-finals-9-24-2017.html |title=SHOWBUZZDAILY's Top 150 Sunday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 9.24.2017 |last=Metcalf |first=Mitch |accessdate=September 25, 2017 |work=Showbuzz Daily |date=September 26, 2017}}</ref>\n| season6   = 2016\u201317\n| viewers6  = 0.47<ref name=\"S6ratings a\">{{cite web |url=http://tvseriesfinale.com/tv-show/teen-wolf-season-six-ratings/ |title=Teen Wolf: Season Six Ratings |date=September 26, 2017 |work=TV Series Finale |accessdate=July 27, 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n\n==Other media==\n===Book===\n* 2012, [[Nancy Holder]], ''On Fire: A Teen Wolf Novel'', [[Simon & Schuster]], {{ISBN|9781451674477}}\nIn June 2012, MTV Books released the book ''On Fire'', by [[Nancy Holder]]. The cover art features [[Tyler Posey]] with glowing yellow eyes, with a fire red background. The book tells the story of [[Scott McCall]] and the first season of ''[[Teen Wolf (season 1)|Teen Wolf]]''.\n\n===Comic===\nA comic themed upon the show was released in June 2011 by [[Image Comics]].<ref>{{cite web |title=MTV.com - Comic - Teen Wolf #1, pt. 1 |url=http://www.mtv.com/geek/comic/issue/1262/teen-wolf-1-pt-1.jhtml |website=MTV.com |accessdate=July 29, 2012 |date=June 6, 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Accolades==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:95%;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:5%;\"  | Year\n! style=\"width:25%;\" | Award\n! style=\"width:35%;\" | Category\n! style=\"width:20%;\" | Nominee(s)\n! style=\"width:10%;\" | Result\n! style=\"width:5%;\"  | {{abbr|Ref(s)|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | 2011\n| rowspan=\"6\" | [[2011 Teen Choice Awards|Teen Choice Awards]]\n| Breakout Star\n| [[Tyler Posey]]\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref name=\"holly\">{{cite web |title=Teen Choice Awards 2011: 'Pretty Little Liars,' Rebecca Black Added to List of Nominees |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/teen-choice-awards-2011-pretty-212996 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |accessdate=April 7, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| Choice Summer TV Show\n| ''Teen Wolf''\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref name=\"holly\" />\n|-\n| Choice Summer TV Star \u2013 Female\n| [[Crystal Reed]]\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref name=\"holly\" />\n|-\n| Choice Summer TV Star \u2013 Male\n| Tyler Posey\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref name=\"holly\" />\n|-\n| Choice TV Actress: Fantasy/Sci-Fi\n| Crystal Reed\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref name=\"wood\">re{{cite web |last1=Swift |first1=Andy |last2=Swift |first2=Andy |title='The Vampire Diaries' Is Up For 9 Teen Choice Awards! See The Full List Of TV Nominees! |url=http://hollywoodlife.com/2011/06/29/teen-choice-awards-2011-nominees-full-list-vampire-diaries/ |website=Hollywood Life |accessdate=April 7, 2017 |date=June 29, 2011}}</ref>\n|-\n| Choice TV Fantasy/Sci-Fi\n| ''Teen Wolf''\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref name=\"wood\" />\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | 2012\n| [[ALMA Award]]\n| Favorite TV Actor \u2013 Leading Role\n| Tyler Posey\n| {{won}}\n| <ref>{{cite web |title=ALMA Awards 2012: Winners And Show Highlights (VIDEO, PHOTOS) |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/09/21/alma-awards-2012-winners-_n_1905245.html |website=Huffington Post |accessdate=April 7, 2017 |date=September 22, 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Imagen Award]]\n| Best Actor/Television\n| Tyler Posey\n| {{nom}}\n| <re