ow\"| \"One of Those Nights\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cmt.com/videos/lisa-brokop/384780/one-of-those-nights.jhtml|title=CMT : Videos : Lisa Brokop : One Of Those Nights|publisher=[[Country Music Television]]|accessdate=October 14, 2011}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Who Needs You\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cmt.com/videos/lisa-brokop/384850/who-needs-you.jhtml|title=CMT : Videos : Lisa Brokop : Who Needs You|publisher=[[Country Music Television]]|accessdate=October 14, 2011}}</ref>\n| Jim Shea\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"She Can't Save Him\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Michael Merriman\n|-\n| 1996\n! scope=\"row\"| \"West of Crazy\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cmt.com/videos/lisa-brokop/385115/west-of-crazy.jhtml|title=CMT : Videos : Lisa Brokop : West Of Crazy|publisher=[[Country Music Television]]|accessdate=October 14, 2011}}</ref>\n|-\n| 1997\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Two Names on an Overpass\"<br /><small>(with [[Duane Steele]])</small>\n| \n|-\n| 1998\n! scope=\"row\"| \"How Do I Let Go\"\n| \n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2001\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Keep Mom and Dad in Love\"<br /><small>(with [[Hal Ketchum]])</small>\n| rowspan=\"3\"| [[Robert Cuffley]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"I'd Like to See You Try\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Say\"\n|-\n| 2002\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Whiskey and Wine\"\n| \n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2004\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Wildflower\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[Stephano Barberis]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Hey, Do You Know Me\"\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2005\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Ladylike\"\n| \n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Big Picture\"\n| \n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2008\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Break It\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Stephano Barberis\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"November Trees\"\n|-\n| 2011\n! scope=\"row\"| \"One Headlight\" <small>(The Jeffersons)</small>\n| Julian Chojnacki\n|-\n| 2013\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Let It Burn\"\n| Evan Brace\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{Lisa Brokop}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Brokop, Lisa}}\n[[Category:Country music discographies]]\n[[Category:Discographies of Canadian artists]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Artist Discography\n|Artist       = [[Lisa Brokop]]\n|Image        = \n|Studio       = 9\n|Compilation  = \n|Singles      = 35\n|Music videos = 19\n}}\n\nThe '''discography''' for Canadian [[country music|country]] singer  '''[[Lisa Brokop]]''' include nine albums and 35 singles. In 1991, Brokop issued her debut album, ''[[My Love (Lisa Brokop album)|My Love]]'', on the independent label Libre Records in Canada. It was in 1994, Brokop signed with Patriot Records, a label owned by [[Liberty Records]] and released her second album ''[[Every Little Girl's Dream]]'' in both Canada and the United States. The album was certified Gold by the [[Music Canada|CRIA]], for sales of 50,000 copies, in October 1995. ''[[Lisa Brokop (album)|Lisa Brokop]]'' followed in 1996 on [[Capitol Records|Capitol Nashville]], the album's commercial failure in both Canada and U.S. forced Brokop and Capitol to part ways.\n\nIn 1998, Brokop signed with [[Columbia Records]] and released the Canadian only release, ''[[When You Get to Be You]]''. The album was scheduled for release in the United States, but due to all singles failing at radio, the album was never released. ''[[Undeniable (Lisa Brokop album)|Undeniable]]'', was issued in 2000 on the independent Cosmo Records label. Five years after the release of her previous album, Brokop returned with ''[[Hey, Do You Know Me]]'' released in 2005 on [[Curb Records]] in Canada. Brokop's most recent album, ''[[The Patsy Cline Project]]'', was issued in 2015.\n\n==Studio albums==\n===1990s===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:16em;\"| Title\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:18em;\"| Details\n! colspan=\"2\"| Peak positions\n! rowspan=\"2\"| [[Music recording sales certification|Certifications]]\n|- style=\"font-size:smaller;\"\n! width=\"40\"| [[RPM (magazine)|CAN Country]]<br/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bac-lac.gc.ca/eng/discover/films-videos-sound-recordings/rpm/Pages/list.aspx?OCRText=Lisa+Brokop&ChartEn=Country+Albums%2fCDs&|title=Lisa Brokop - Country Albums/CDs|work=[[RPM (magazine)|RPM]]|accessdate=April 22, 2019}}</ref>\n! width=\"40\"| [[Top Country Albums|US Country]]<br/><ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.billboard.com/music/lisa-brokop/chart-history/country-albums|title=Lisa Brokop - Country Albums|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=April 22, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''My Love''\n| \n* Release date: 1991\n* Label: Libre Records\n* Formats: [[Compact disc|CD]], [[Compact Cassette|cassette]]\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Every Little Girl's Dream]]''\n| \n* Release date: September 6, 1994\n* Label: [[Liberty Records|Patriot Records]]\n* Formats: CD, cassette\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| align=\"left\"|\n* [[Music Canada|CAN]]: Gold<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.musiccanada.com/GPSearchResult.aspx?st=&ica=False&sa=Lisa%20Brokop&sl=&smt=0&sat=-1&ssb=Artist|title=Gold & Platinum Search - Lisa Brokop|publisher=[[Music Canada]]|accessdate=August 9, 2011}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Lisa Brokop (album)|Lisa Brokop]]''\n| \n* Release date: February 20, 1996\n* Label: [[Capitol Records|Capitol Nashville]]\n* Formats: CD, cassette\n| 18\n| 74\n| \n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[When You Get to Be You]]''\n| \n* Release date: July 21, 1998\n* Label: [[Columbia Records]]\n* Formats: CD, cassette\n| 21\n| \u2014\n|\n|-\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"font-size:8pt\"| \"\u2014\" denotes releases that did not chart\n|-\n|}\n\n===2000s and 2010s===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:16em;\"| Title\n! style=\"width:18em;\"| Details\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Undeniable (Lisa Brokop album)|Undeniable]]''\n| \n* Release date: 2000\n* Label: Cosmo Records\n* Formats: CD, cassette\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Hey, Do You Know Me]]''\n| \n* Release date: January 11, 2005\n* Label: [[Curb Records|Asylum-Curb Records]]\n* Formats: CD, [[Music download|digital download]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Beautiful Tragedy (Lisa Brokop album)|Beautiful Tragedy]]''\n| \n* Release date: August 19, 2008\n* Label: Ellbea Music\n* Formats: CD, digital download\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''The Jeffersons, Vol. 1''<br/>{{small|(with [[Paul Jefferson]])}}\n| \n* Release date: June 7, 2011\n* Label: [[Royalty Records]]\n* Formats: CD, digital download\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[The Patsy Cline Project]]''\n|\n* Release date: August 1, 2015\n* Label: Ellbea Music\n* Formats: CD, digital download\n|}\n\n==Singles==\n===1990s===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:18em;\"| Single\n! colspan=\"2\"| Peak positions\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Album\n|- style=\"font-size:smaller;\"\n! width=\"45\"| [[RPM (magazine)|CAN Country]]<br><ref name=\"Canada Country\">Peak chart positions for country singles of Lisa Brokop in Canada:\n*Singles released 1990 to 2000 \u2013 {{cite magazine|url=http://www.bac-lac.gc.ca/eng/discover/films-videos-sound-recordings/rpm/Pages/list.aspx?OCRText=Lisa+Brokop&ChartEn=Country+Singles&|title=Lisa Brokop - Country Tracks|magazine=[[RPM (magazine)|RPM]]|accessdate=April 22, 2019}}\n*\"Wildflower\" \u2013 {{cite journal|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-RandR/2000s/2004/RR-2004-09-17.pdf|title=Canada Country Top 30|journal=Radio & Records|date=September 17, 2004}}\n*\"Hey, Do You Know Me\" \u2013 {{cite journal|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-RandR/2000s/2005/RR-2005-02-11.pdf|title=Canada Country Top 30|journal=Radio & Records|date=February 11, 2005}}\n*\"Big Picture\" \u2013 {{cite journal|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-RandR/2000s/2005/RR-2005-10-28.pdf|title=Canada Country Top 30|journal=Radio & Records|date=October 28, 2005}}\n*Singles released since 2008 \u2013 {{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/music/lisa-brokop/chart-history/canada-country|title=Lisa Brokop - Canada Country|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=April 22, 2019}} </ref>\n! width=\"45\"| [[Hot Country Songs|US Country]]<br><ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.billboard.com/music/lisa-brokop/chart-history/country-songs|title=Lisa Brokop - Country Songs|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=April 22, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 1990\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Daddy, Sing to Me]]\"\n| 10\n| \u2014\n| align=\"left\" rowspan=\"5\"| ''My Love''\n|-\n| 1991\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Old Mister Moon\"\n| 34\n| \u2014\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 1992\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Time to Come Back Home\"\n| 40\n| \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"My Love\"\n| 34\n| \u2014\n|-\n| 1993\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Country Girl\"\n| 16\n| \u2014\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 1994\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Stand by Your Man]]\"\n| 88\n| \u2014\n| align=\"left\"| ''Harmony Cats'' {{small|(soundtrack)}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Give Me a Ring Sometime (song)|Give Me a Ring Sometime]]\"\n| 12\n| 52\n| align=\"left\" rowspan=\"4\"| ''Every Little Girl's Dream''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Take That\"\n| 34\n| 52\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 1995\n! scope=\"row\"| \"One of Those Nights\"\n| 31\n| 64\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Who Needs You\"\n| 58\n| 60\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"She Can't Save Him\"\n| 63\n| 55\n| align=\"left\" rowspan=\"3\"| ''Lisa Brokop''\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 1996\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Before He Kissed Me\"\n| 82\n| 63\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"West of Crazy\"\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 1998\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[How Do I Let Go]]\"\n| 19\n| 59\n| align=\"left\" rowspan=\"6\"| ''When You Get to Be You''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"What's Not to Love\"\n| 20\n| \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"When You Get to Be You\"\n| 57\n| 64\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 1999\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Ain't Enough Roses\"\n| \u2014\n| 65\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Better Off Broken]]\"\n| 8\n| \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Cool Summer Night\"\n| 53\n| \u2014\n|-\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"